cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is about artificial intelligence and game theory, specifically about learning approximate Nash equilibrium in imperfect-information games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and deep learning, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. Game theory is a key component of the paper, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a possible category. The use of Monte Carlo tree search and parallel architecture suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories.
